726765f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - 58th Street
726765f-a.text:
(1)
Grand Ave., south side, east of 58th Street (Rust Street), showing
in the center of view, in order, the homes of Cord Meyer Sr. and Jr.
These homes were both built by the elder Cord Meyer. The house partially
shown, in the foreground, does not appear in the 1929 Queens Atlas.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing a close up of center of view seen in No. 1.
January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
